Dr. Jill Biden, wife of former Vice President Joe Biden, will be delivering two commencement addresses this spring. On May 15th, she will address the graduating class at Salve Regina University in Newport, Rhode Island. Salve Regina is a Catholic, coeducational university that focuses on arts and sciences. On May 19th, Dr. Biden will speak at Montgomery County Community College's 44th Commencement Ceremony in King of Prussia, Pennsylvania. Montgomery County Community College has campuses in Blue Bell and Pottstown and is known for its award-winning faculty and commitment to student success. Dr. Biden has been an educator for 30 years and continues to teach English courses at a community college in Northern Virginia. She has previously delivered commencement addresses at the University of Delaware and Columbia University Teachers' College.